GRAPEVINE VIRUSES: USA, PAKISTAN
********************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

In this posting:
[1] _Grapevine red blotch virus_ - USA: germplasm collection, California
[2] _Grapevine Pinot gris virus_ - Pakistan: 1st report

******
[1] _Grapevine red blotch virus_ - USA: germplasm collection, California
Date: Wed 20 Dec 2017
Source: University of California, Foundation Plant Services (FPS) [edited]
http://fps.ucdavis.edu/newsarticle.cfm?newsid=19


_Grapevine red blotch virus_ (GRBV) has been found in the Russell Ranch [Foundation] Vineyard (RRV). Five of 4132 vines tested positive for GRBV [and] have been removed and destroyed. One vine tested positive in the Classic Foundation [vineyard and] was removed. Every grapevine in RRV has been tested. _Vitis_ spp. in proximity to RRV have been tested; positive vines have been removed.

All vines related to GRBV positives tested negative, indicating that this is a field transmission of GRBV. Sprays targeting the vector have been applied. RRV has been tested for GRBV since 2013 and this is the 1st time it has been detected. Preliminary sequence analysis showed 99 per cent identity to GRBV isolates from 2 different groups, which indicates separate infection events.

Material from the plants was distributed prior to the last negative test date, indicating that [it] was likely GRBV-free at distribution. The one customer who received material from the vines has been contacted. All vines in RRV will be tested for GRBV annually by composite testing. Classic Foundation [vineyard] will be subject to regular testing as well as prior to distribution.

[Byline: Deborah Golino]

--
Communicated by:
Dr N Habili
Waite Diagnostics, University of Adelaide
